-- Amsurg to expand into physician services with $2.35 bln deal
-- By Esha Dey in Bangalore
-- Thu May 29, 2014 06:14AM EDT
-- None



May 29 (Reuters) - Surgery center operator Amsurg Corp <AMSG.O> said it would buy Sheridan Healthcare from private equity firm Hellman & Friedman in a cash and stock deal valued at about $2.35 billion to enter the outsourced physician services market.

The acquisition is expected to immediately add to Amsurg's adjusted earnings and cash flow, the company said in a statement. [ID:nBw1kFGlda]